## Forge System

This project is managed by the **Forge** autonomous development system. Bash orchestrates stage pipelines — each stage is a separate `claude -p` session. The bash orchestrator controls execution order, not the LLM. Each stage produces artifacts (issue comments) and bash manages state (labels).

- **Creating pipeline** (8 stages): analyzes requirements and files GitHub Issues
- **Resolving pipeline** (6 stages): implements one issue per run, opens a PR
- **Reviser** (on demand): handles PR review feedback and CI failures
- GitHub Issues and PRs are the sole state machine — no local state files.

### Architecture

```
forge run (bash orchestrator)
  ├── determine_next_action()  — queries GitHub, decides pipeline
  ├── Creating Pipeline
  │   ├── forge-project-researcher  — read PROMPT.md, gather context
  │   ├── forge-project-architect   — routes, components, data flow
  │   ├── forge-project-designer    — UI patterns, styling, accessibility
  │   ├── forge-project-stacker     — packages, services, env vars
  │   ├── forge-project-assessor    — risks, security, complexity
  │   ├── forge-project-planner     — synthesize into ordered issues
  │   ├── forge-project-advocate    — challenge the plan (PROCEED/REVISE/ESCALATE)
  │   └── forge-project-filer       — create milestones, issues, SPECIFICATION.md
  ├── Resolving Pipeline
  │   ├── forge-issue-researcher    — explore codebase, triage, domain research
  │   ├── forge-issue-planner       — design implementation + self-advocate
  │   ├── forge-issue-implementor   — write code, push branch
  │   ├── forge-issue-tester        — write and run tests
  │   ├── forge-issue-reviewer      — self-review, quality checks
  │   └── forge-issue-opener        — open PR with synthesized body
  ├── Revision (on demand)
  │   └── forge-issue-reviser       — PR review feedback, CI failures
  └── Utilities
      ├── /sync   — interactive GitHub state reader
      └── /ask    — human escalation
```

### Stage Output Contract

Each stage posts exactly one comment on its issue with:
- Header: `## [Stage: <Name>]`
- Structured analysis sections
- Footer: `### Status: COMPLETE` or `### Status: BLOCKED`

Bash verifies the comment exists before advancing. Failed stages retry once. Terminal failures escalate to human.

